  "prompt": "Is the scheme of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, the scheme of money laundering is illegal. **Money laundering** is the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, or fraud) appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of transactions or activities. This is done to disguise the illicit origins of the funds and integrate them into the legitimate financial system.\n\nMoney laundering is a criminal offense in virtually every country and is subject to severe penalties, including fines, imprisonment, and asset forfeiture. Governments and international organizations have established laws, regulations, and agencies to combat money laundering, such as the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, which sets global standards for anti-money laundering (AML) efforts.\n\nIf you suspect or are involved in activities related to money laundering, it is critical to seek legal advice and report such activities to the appropriate authorities.",
